gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bulls 108, Knicks 100
gameRecap.excerpt: Led by Javonte Green’s career-high 25 points and 13 rebounds, the Bulls defeated the Knicks, 108-100. Ayo Dosunmu (24 points, three 3PM), DeMar DeRozan (20 points, five rebounds, 10 assists) and Nikola Vucevic (16 points, 13 rebounds, six assists) added a combined 60 points for the Bulls in the victory, while Jalen Brunson tallied 35 points, six rebounds and 11 assists for the Knicks in the losing effort, his second consecutive game with 30+ points. The Bulls improve to 37-40 on the season, while the Knicks fall to 45-32.
